==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lampblack
<hw>Lamp"black`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Lamp</ets> +
<ets>black</ets>.]</ety> <def>The fine impalpable soot obtained from the
smoke of carbonaceous substances which have been only partly burnt, as
in the flame of a smoking lamp. It consists of finely divided carbon,
with sometimes a very small proportion of various impurities. It is used
as an ingredient of printers' ink, and various black pigments and
cements.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lamper eel</ent>⟦br⟧
